result.execSummary:
The defendant Josue Ruben Velez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Violate/Harassment Restraining Order, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.125(7).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Josue Ruben Velez in court with attorney Colin P. McGinn.  Defendant Josue Ruben Velez in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Court sentenced defendant to serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction CONCURRENT to any sentence with credit for 30 days served FOR A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court ordered the defendant to pay restitution in the amount of $330.00 to Angelita U. by 03-06-2017 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.  Court ordered the defendant to submit a DNA sample.  Court ordered defendant to pay ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES by 03-06-2017 or, as a penalty if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.  Appeal 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Attorney Colin P. McGinn in court, defendant Josue Ruben Velez not in court, in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Case calendared for plea/sentencing hearing.  The victim was present in court and ready to make a statement.  Court ordered case adjourned for jury trial in Branch 21.  Jury trial scheduled for May 4, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Colin P. McGinn in court, defendant Josue Ruben Velez not in court, in custody.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Court waives the appearance of the defendant for this hearing only.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 21.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for February 2, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision.  ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY to be monitored by drug testing.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Angelita U. or the address listed on the criminal complaint.

Defendant Josue Ruben Velez in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Defendant Josue Ruben Velez in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm

Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for January 13, 2016 at 08:30 am.
